# Build output and regenerated goldens are NOT versioned: Oracle A re-captures
# goldens from a fresh origin/main-built bd on every run (that is the whole point
# — the reference is the branch's own merge base, not a pinned snapshot).
/target/
/testdata/
# Cargo.lock IS committed (not ignored): this crate produces two [[bin]] targets,
# so pinning the lockfile keeps the gate reproducible — serde/regex/tempfile do not
# drift with upstream releases between CI runs.
